description: In a story told entirely from first-person perspective, Alfred Pennyworth searches for Batman, who's in the midst of a fight for his life! Can Alfred get there in time?
name: First-Person Shooter

description: Part 3 of 6.

Bo goes head to head with the "Roswell" gang, while his body still lies in a coma!

It's plushy teddy vs. alien mutant gang warfare... can you dig it?!?!
name: Part 2

description: A collection of African folktales adapted to comics.
name: Africa Edition

description:
In the third installment of Dan In Space. Joules has to race against the clock to save Dan and stop the Lorkis.

At the edge of explored space, technician Dan Johnson is stuck in a dead-end job. As melancholy as his life is, Dan is about to go on an adventure. He is not prepared, he is not armed, and he's running out of coffee.

Edge of a Sword

Blutstein becomes better acquainted with certain members of the diplomatic party, and the Count begins to change the terms of his agreement with the Department.

Dawn of the Morningstar - Part 2 of 3

Sara Morningstar comes face to face with the mysterious inhabitants of Grimstone Manor and learns the true meaning of Madame Hildegarde's ominous warning. But evil lurks in the shadows, and it has devious plans for the young heroine.
name: Dawn of the Morningstar Part 2 of 3

description:
Downfall: Part 2

Downfall continues as an unexpected attack hurls the Heroes of Echo Company unprotected into the vacuum of space. Sinbad, Robin Hood, Lancelot, Hua Mulan, Samson, Wild Bill, Musashi and Ulysses are in a fight for their life.
name: Downfall: Part 2

description: All the clues have led Sully to a seemingly-normal nightclub. What strange bodies does this place have hidden in the floorboards, and what will happen to Sully's mind when he uncovers them?

Daydreams and Phone Calls

In MAKESHIFT MIRACLE part four, Colby tries to resume his normal life, but a shared dream with Iris intrudes, opening a communication portal with a threatening figure from her past.
name: Chapter 10: Darker Place

volume.name: Makeshift Miracle: The Girl From Nowhere

description: The fallout from the "Crisis" issue brings back a Purrrrrrfect foil. Look for the cat-tactic Julie Newmar and Eartha Kitt as they team up with Adam West's catman.

The Devils Luck

Following Coles attempted suicide; he awakens in the psychiatric ward of a hospital, with no recollection of the incident. The psychiatrist Doctor Zane questions Cole and learns that the dead agent he investigated was a close friend from the academy named Tommy. As Dr. Zane digs deeper, he finds out that Cole’s mother was killed in a boating accident, and his father was murdered when he was only nine years old.
name: The Devils Luck

description: Trying to protect his recently acquired mind control technology, Shiwan Khan (known to the world as Geng King, president of Nissteco) narrowly avoids death-thanks to the Shadow, oddly enough. But danger continues to loom and the Light grows larger and more deadly, vying for that Nissteco mind control device. In this clash of villains, the Shadow must not only keep himself alive, but also the rest of the world!
name: Shadows and Light Part 5: Saving Grace

description: Clark Kent has met the ring’s former wearer, plus Earth’s current Green Lantern has volunteered to be a mentor. But he still doesn’t understand his role in the struggle to come.
name: Part 3 of 12

description:
After being sucked into a wormhole on his first trip into space, Bops the Astrochimp emerged from the space anomaly a smarter, more evolved chimp. Unfortunately, he also wound up on the opposite side of the galaxy, stranded on a planet in thrall to the evil Overlord Jardu Krush. With help from a local named Max, Bops risks everything to break into the heavily controlled Tiklopis Way Station to meet with a shady character who promises him information about his lost spaceship.

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
ACover ARamon Salas1
BCover BRamon Salas (p) & Ulises PadillaMissing
Dr. Vega catches up to Alpha and Beta, while Bryce ponders Operation Paragon's future.

Serialized from the pages of Bust magazine and Unlovable Book 1, the sometimes ordinary, sometimes humiliating, often poignant and frequently hilarious exploits of '80s teen underdog Tammy Pierce: big hair, boogers, boys and other high school pitfalls. Tammy finds a hair on her chin, gets to make some prank phone calls and hope that her fake date with Ken Olsen is the real deal.
name: Kute

description: One of the Blue Mountain campers is discovered convulsing and clawing her bunk to pieces, pushing Jeremy and April to question whether the Beast of Blue Mountain’s pranks are really pranks at all. But with the Bonnie Bennett’s help, the truth is revealed!
name: Beast of Blue Mountain Part 2 of 2

description:
Slaughter in the Tower of Sloth

With no solid leads and a third murder involving a wealthy fat cat, pressure is building for Daniels and Harvey to find the killer. Edward Smittz meets in secret with some old business colleagues. Edward fears that theirs pasts are coming back to haunt them.
name: Slaughter in the Tower of Sloth

description:
In a world where witches have declared war against humanity, the surviving human population has gathered specialists with the power to hunt and destroy witches.

Tasha Godspell, also known as the "Magic Marksman," is one of the best Witch Busters there is. Along with his sword-wielding Jack-o'-Lantern partner known as Halloween, Tasha puts his magical training and weaponry to good use, in his constant battles against witches. And yet, he cannot bring himself to fully hate the very witches he is tasked to destroy.
name: Vol. 9

description: During the 1960's, Grant Worth's ability to control machines made him a legendary figure in Detroit. But when Worth's powers become obsolete because of society's own progress, he is forced to discover what happens when a superhero can no longer be super...
name: Chapter IV

description:
While her parents are abroad in India, Crystal "christie" Hope turns her restless, curious mind to the cases of her uncle Sherlock Holmes. That is, when she is no occupied by such hardships as dancing lessons, poetry recitations, horrid playmates, and marauding dodo birds.

Dark secrets emerge from the past of Christie's loyal maids, as well as surprising revelations about the Hope family; and Christie herself must confront her future as a noble, high-society lady.

Christie's cases in this book include:

The Adventure of the Flying Dancer

The Adventure of the Famous Trainer
name: Vol. 6

description:
While her parents are abroad in India, Crystal "christie" Hope turns her restless, curious mind to the cases of her uncle Sherlock Holmes. That is, when she is no occupied by such hardships as dancing lessons, poetry recitations, horrid playmates, and marauding dodo birds.

Dark secrets emerge from the past of Christie's loyal maids, as well as surprising revelations about the Hope family; and Christie herself must confront her future as a noble, high-society lady. Meanwhile, Christie races to solve the greatest-and most deadly-mystery she's ever encountered before her parents return home!

Christie's cases in this book include:

The Adventure of the Giant Rat of Sumatra
name: Vol. 7
Stvari o kojima se ne laže

person_credits.name: Eiichiro Oda
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, inker, cover

description:
Takashi has been dating Haruhiko, his boss at the flower hall flower shop, for a week now, yet they haven't made any progress at all! Whether it's finally making love or moving in together, Takashi is scared of taking their relationship any further. It doesn't help matters any when their clueless coworker and his lover keep butting in to give him bad advice, but Takashi just can't help himself when his sneaky lover is so determined to have him. Would it really be so bad to give in and do all those scary things couples do? Blooming Darling continues the sweet love story of Takashi and Haruhiko. Tears are shed and hearts pound while Takashi comes to terms with the more x-rated activities in their relationship, but Haruhiko is more than happy to lead the way as they learn to share their lives and love.

Contents

  • Blooming Darling
  • Which reminds me, I forgot
name: Vol. 1

description: Ace's report to the government about the events of ACE KILROY: SEASON 1.

While searching for her missing sister, Ruby, Lindsay visits the office of Alessio Capelli, where her sister was employed as his personal assistant. Alessio is a slick divorce attorney, while Lindsay is a counselor who works on reconciling marriages. Their natures clash like natural enemies that would make great reading on any of the tabloids. Lindsay embarrassingly finds herself taken by Alessio's fine body. She discovers that he was planning to dismiss Ruby as she is MIA. In order to save Ruby's job, she must accompany him to the Caribbean to fill-in as his personal assistant!
name: Vol. 1

description: Bluewater Productions proudly presents the first four issues of "COMICS," the biography series about stand-ups, sitcom stars, and comedians who have made a huge impact on popular culture. Included in this volume are the illustrated life stories of George Carlin, Lucille Ball, and The Three Stooges, as well as the history of Saturday Night Live. This volume also features an exclusive biography of Eddie Murphy-- available ONLY in this collection!
name: Volume One

description:
The beautiful illustrator, Tatsuki, has a problem. No one can see past his good looks. That is until freelance writer, Mikami, steps into the picture! Of course, Tatsuki thinks Mikami is just like the others, but soon finds out nothing could be further from the truth. It turns out Mikami doesn't even like men. As they spend more time together, Tatsuki starts developing certain feelings... Will he be able to show Mikami how he feels? And, how will Mikami respond...? Find out in this manga by Mui Hatori!

Contents

  • At the End of A Cold Night
  • Conditions of Happiness
  • Conditions of Happiness Extra
  • Symmetrical Desire
  • Resistance In the Wind
  • Memories of the Sky
name: Vol. 1

description:
The year is 2095. Global warming has forced the sea levels to rise (as well as the salt table) shrinking the Earths limited pastoral and arable land. There is not enough global land resources to feed the world's bulging population!

The free world has descended into chaos and crime, which brings about new world order instability - how can America police the world when they cannot take care of their own back yard?

The Security Council sanctions a secret program that genetically and physically alters an elite team of crime fighters in an attempt to crush the gangs that are violently taking control of the country.

Not everyone sees the project altruistically and the premature unleashing of the projects subjects creates more chaos than they were designed to control!

Who is really behind the project and what is the real reason for its existence?

The advertisement agency started by Polly's father has been bought out by Damon Doukakis. Why would the leader of such a large corporation choose this tiny company as his target? The workers are baffled, but Polly knows exactly why: Damon is trying to punish Polly's father for eloping with his sister, Arianna. Damon declares he will fire all of the executives, and also warns Polly that she will no longer have nepotism on her side. Damon's arrogance and Polly's determination to protect her company pit them against each other-but one night, sparks of passion end up leading to intimacy.
name: Vol. 1

description: Lovato began her career on the Disney Channel, starring alongside fellow pop sensations the Jonas Brothers, before rocketing to music stardom with two Billboard chart-topping albums. The inspiring young singer is set to host the second season of The X Factor this fall. Chronicling her early years, through her rising career, to the present, "Fame: Demi Lovato" is a must have for Lovato fans everywhere. 1st time in Spanish!

The One and Only

Crime is everywhere. Evil is all around us!

But there's one man who would do anything... A man with no fear, no regret, no hesitation. A man ready to give his life for JUSTICE !

Maribel has a crush on her cousin's boyfriend, Leonidas, the Greek billionaire who constantly makes the tabloid headlines. She has a passionate one night stand with him, the day her cousin dies in a car crash! Maribel is convinced that she is nothing but a poor replacement for her cousin, yet she can't help feeling hopelessly destroyed by Leonidas's cold goodbye the morning after their tryst. Two years later, she is unexpectedly reunited with Leonidas, but she has a secret that she can never reveal to him. She had given birth to his child. Now, the truth has leaked to the paparazzi and tabloids alike!
name: Vol. 1

description: "You won't leave this game until every part of you belongs to me." Sergio Torrente, an Italian businessman, is surprised at who he sees in the surveillance camera. The mysterious person making moves every night against his challenging chess display at the office turns out to be a cleaner clad in a shabby uniform. But how could such a beautiful woman be just a cleaner? Drawn to the mysterious woman, Sergio summons her and declares that she will play a game of chess with him every night, starting this very day!
name: Vol. 1

description: Jason has the mythological Golden Fleece firmly in his grasp. Now learn what happens as the Argonauts sail home and bleakly discover that they have been manipulated in the plans of Zeus who prepares for a celestial war that will break Olympus apart!

The Merciful is a comic book series set in our grim, but not to distant future. It chronicles an ensemble of characters that are struggling to do what they think is right while the world is crumbling around them.

The first of five omnibus books collecting the award-nominated super-soap comic series!

Doctor O gathers a new superteam to fight his nemesis, Anathema. But can they stop Anathema before she takes her revenge on their friends and family - and finally, on themselves?

This book collects the first 8 issues of The O Men, including the first two story arcs, 'Little Earthquakes' and 'Frenzy'.
name: Book One

volume.name: The O Men: The Complete Story

description: Newly single Caro Cartwright has decided that when it comes to life (and men), ordinary is good. Until her best friend, Princess Lotty, begs her to stage a diversion by masquerading as Prince Philippe of Montluce's latest squeeze Playboy Philippe thinks their attempt is doomed. How can he pretend to be in love with someone like Caro, who's so unglamorous? Then Caro starts winning hearts left, right and center including his. Can Philippe convince Caro not to settle for normal but for an extraordinary life as princess of Montluce?
name: Vol. 1

description:
First published in the cult British kid's comic Oink! back in 1986, Psycho Gran is the psychotically demented brain-child of cartoonist and comic book editor, David Leach - winner of Channel Four's Come Dine With Me, editor and writer of the Wallace and Gromit newspaper strip and the Adventure Time comic magazine and editor of Roman Dirge's Lenore. David is also the co-creator of cult 1990's strip The Driver for British comic Toxic!

Psycho Gran (or Psycho Besta as she's known in Norway) is a five-foot high, mauve-haired, bespectacled, psychotic granny with a pan-dimensional, sentient handbag called Percy, a flying dog called Archie and a pathological loathing of rudeness.

Join her for an all-new, 29-page, full-color journey into a surrealist slapstick world of rampaging kaiju, neo-Nazi skinheads, bag-snatchers, death-row inmates, explosive diarrhoea and those annoying SOBs who will insist on using their bloody cellphones in cinemas.

She puts the Old into Old Skool Kicking!

Amongst the stars live a powerful race of creatures, forged from dreams, born from the cosmos.

Carnelion, with his little companion Indy, arrives at the StarFortress of Atolista to train to become a StarKnight.

Crisis of the Cerulean King Part 1

Pythro, an Adept of the Tribrachidium Sodality, is sent on a mission to discover why the city of Ostenarth has been forsaken by the the great river spirit known as the Cerulean King. If he fails...the city and it's people may perish.
name: Crisis of the Cerulean King Part 1

description: Welcome to Victorian London. The year is 1888 and the city has never seen such peril. Danger is on every street corner and evil lurks in the hearts of every man, woman and child. Enter Theodore Paulsen, a well groomed gentleman and pillar of society. After receiving a strange invitation to the sleepy village of "Fenton's Green", he leaves the darkness of London behind and sets out on the journey which will change his life forever.
name: Part One of Three

description:
Day 1

I took a short (three and a half days!) trip to Iceland in December 2012. Before I went, I thought, "It'd be fun to make some comics about my trip after I get back, depending on how much there is to talk about." Well, it turns out I have a LOT to talk about!
name: Day 1

description: Peter tries to rob the Tooth Fairy (after all, she's got to be carrying a lot of cash -- think of how many people lose their tooth on the average night and get a dollar), but instead catches his Dad... or did he?

An unjustly condemned man cheats death in the gas chamber by using occult power to transform into toxic gas. A psychologically troubled FBI agent is ordered to apprehend him but turns rogue and threatens to destroy his last tie to humanity in a sadistic game of cat and mouse.
name: GN

volume.name: No Need for Tenchi! Part Nine

description: A flip book

volume.name: Married With Children: Quantum Quartet, The Big Wrap-Up

name: The Man of Too Many Faces

description: Welcome to Templar, Arizona. Ben Kowalski is a recent transplant from Yakima, Washington, a writer for a local alternative paper, and a dedicated hermit. In two months in Templar, his only friendships so far have been forced upon him: The acquaintance of a kindergartner named Zoradysis, and the determined attentions of his overbearing and flamboyantly obscene neighbor, Reagan. He needs to get out more, and he's gonna. Whether he likes it or not.
name: The Great Outdoors

description:
Curio lives in King Street, Templar's ritziest neighborhood. So does her best friend, Tuesday. Her penthouse apartment should be enough for anyone, but young and aimless, Curio longs for the validation of the Low People, Templar's workin' stiffs, and the envy of her well-to-do peers in the bargain.

Meanwhile, in Riverside, the spillover from a downtown riot ends up on Ben's windowsill. He gets over it. Nobody else does, but there are worse things out there than being mistaken for someone interesting.
name: The Mob Goes Wild

description:
Gene's family are in town, and his friends get to learn all about the Jakeskin, the survivalist cult they belong to. When his friends aren't around, however, they've got some strange plans for Gene.

Scipio debates life decisions with Pippi and Reagan, and has a rough day at work.

Ben visits Dr. Bash--the drunk he helped back home in the previous chapter--and meets someone new.
name: And a Stick to Beat the Devil With

description:
The Elliots run afoul of the Jakeskin--Gene's family--causing bad things to happen to a whole bunch of innocent street people.

Ben hangs out at Reagan's workplace, the "adult store" Kingdom Come.

Tuesday's rivalry with Nicky Collision heats up, and she finds some new ammo at Moze and Sunny's place.

Scipio has found out what's up with Pippi, and neither of them handles it very well.
name: Trouble Every Day

description:
Atomic Robo investigates cryptid sightings near the old Nazi space program, "Science City," buried deep in the Venezuelan wilderness. Meanwhile, a mysterious package is delivered to Tesladyne - from Hashima Island Quarantine Zone. Is it from ALAN? Majestic 12? Or something else entirely? If only the title could shed some light on this!

Note: The digital edition (9/26/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Volume Eight

volume.name: Atomic Robo and the Savage Sword of Dr. Dinosaur

description:
The evil power of Void Stalin refuses to die even after the failed assassination attempt of 1865! Time Lincoln traces disturbances to 1968 and discovers a dark force known only as "The Man" has been hard at work, corrupting and consolidating strength against anything that could stop its plans of dominating the future! Time Lincoln has to work fast, because the Void Shadow's next target is Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.!

Note: The digital edition (9/26/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Grant discovers the truth about the Pillar's sabotage, tearing his team apart just as they are launched into a dimension of mad gravity and violent monkey ghosts! How do you survive insanity when you can't trust anyone around you?
name: Lies, Lies, Lies

description:
The Law on the beach! The cameras are on Dredd as he patrols the coastline of Mega-City Two, but what happens when disaster strikes at an immigration checkpoint's Citizenship Pageant? And what about the enormous man-eating shrimp that's terrorizing what used to be the California waterfront?

ARegular CoverUlises Farinas1
SubSubscription CoverE. J. Su2

Note: The digital edition (9/26/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: City of Courts Part 3 of 5: Beach Blanket Justice

description: This is it! The dramatic debut of supernatural crime saga “Eastsiders” by Pj Perez and António Brandão! The riotous return of The Devastator in “Hard Time” by Russell Lissau and Justin Castanenda. And a lesson about sexual harassment from the Freedom Team by Alex De-Gruchy and Mike Kennedy.
The gun battle with the mercs leaves Michael’s car crashed and Michael and Tabitha for dead. Elsewhere, Katherine gets a huge surprise when she meets the mercs’ employer.

Michael and the car (KITT) track the mercs to an abandoned FLAGG Foundation safe house where they are caught in an ambush. KITT takes more serious damage and, too late, Michael learns the identity of the mercs’ employer.

How dangerous can one man be? That’s what Hawke and his team are about to find out when the captured Granger escapes. Worse the seasoned merc has a plan to kill Hawke and all of his friends using the still crashed and disabled Airwolf!

The Airwolf team begins a desperate hunt for Dr. Moffit who has gone off the grid. Little do they realize that Moffit is inching closer and closer to his ultimate goal of revenge on the United States for their part in a tragedy that change the man forever!

In BLAZE BROTHERS No. 2 - “Traitors Amongst Us” - Jack and Billy Blaze are ruthlessly betrayed by a fellow brother. This devious act literally rips Jack and Billy’s lives apart and leaves one of their very own near death..."WE WERE SET UP FOR SOMETHING WE DID NOT DO! SOMEONE PLACED A TWO MILLION DOLLAR CONTRACT ON OUR HEADS. NOW EVERY MURDERING, KILLING, SCUM BUCKET IN THE CITY IS OUT TO PUT A BULLET IN OUR HEADS. SO LISTEN, AND LISTEN CLOSELY - IF THEY WANT BLOOD, WE WILL GIVE THEM BLOOD... BUCKETS OF IT!!!"
name: Traitors Amongst Us

description:
How quickly the tides change... One day the world is your oyster and enemies cringe and run at the very sound of your name, and then the next day you become the hunted; Labeled Enemy Number 1 by Yamamoto's crime organization.

A briefcase given to Jack and Billy Blaze to guard with their lives is stolen, leaving Mr. Yamamoto to think the brothers pulled a fast one. The Blaze Brothers are left with no choice but to defend themselves at all cost as Yamamoto's wrath begins.

"WE WERE SET UP FOR SOMETHING WE DID NOT DO! SOMEONE PLACED A TWO MILLION DOLLAR CONTRACT ON OUR HEADS. NOW EVERY MURDERING, KILLING, SCUM BUCKET IN THE CITY IS OUT TO PUT A BULLET IN OUR HEADS. SO LISTEN, AND LISTEN CLOSELY - IF THEY WANT BLOOD, WE WILL GIVE THEM BLOOD... BUCKETS OF IT!!!"
name: We Ride, They Die

description: Evil Inc Monthly is a pre-release of all of the Evil Inc strips scheduled for the upcoming month -- plus a special bonus feature created from the archive of the comic. Evil Inc is a corporation run for super-villains by super-villains.
name: The Ul'Thax Proposal

description: Evil Inc is a corporation run for super-villains by super-villains. The Evil Inc monthly comic is a pre-release of all of the Evil Inc strips scheduled for the upcoming month -- plus a special bonus feature created from the archive of the comic.
name: Sweetheart Deal: Part Two of the Ul'Thax Saga

description: Holy Macanoli! Punky gets a tour of a magical place full of beautiful costumes and exotic artifacts -- Henry's camera studio! Henry sure seems like a grumpy old guy, but that can't keep Punky's spirit -- or Brandon's tail -- down! But how could an old photographer like Henry take care of a little girl like Punky? It just doesn't seem possible... What're Punky and Brandon going to do?
name: Punky and Grumpy

description: Trapped under tons of rubble Rampage reflects on the day he received his powers. Rampage must find the inner strength buried within his memories to escape the wreckage and somehow save the day.

The nefarious Mr. Walters is holding all the chips. He’s got Rampage’s friend Brandy James and his personal assistant Kim held hostage. Rampage means to save them but first he’s has to run a gauntlet rematch against the Four Seasons, the team of villains that handily defeated him earlier. First up Winter!

Lisa's taking her fashion vlog from a little webisode on BayTube to a chance at stardom... She's entering a contest to be the Fashion Channel's next student commentator! But when her ratings slip, her only chance is accidental video of Jessie's wardrobe malfunction! Will Lisa do the right thing and take the video down, or fulfill her life-long dream of being on TV -- even if it's at Jessie's expense?

Synopsis

Lisa ends her Baytube fashion vlog and announces to the group that she is in a contest to see whose channel gets the most hits. The winner gets to be Fashion Channel's Student Commentator. She enlists her friends to model some of the fashions she wants to highlight. Screech, of course, bungles the wardrobe and clothes end up all over the floor.

Lisa later finds out that she is in eleventh place. All of her ideas to nab new views fail until Jessie walks into the Max. Jessie, it seems, has tucked her skirt into her underwear. She slams some books down (after studying for an academic decathlon) and somehow takes a video of her panty faux pas and somehow automatically uploads it to Lisa's Baytube page. The video is a hit and bumps Lisa up to tenth place by the next day. Jessie is mortified that her butt got posted to the internet. Even worse are the cat-calls she gets. She orders Lisa to take the video down. Lisa promises to take it down, but then notices that she is now in third place.

At the Max, Lisa battles with herself whether to take the video down. Her friends push her to remove it. She nearly agrees until Mr. Belding informs the group that Lisa is now in first place. Lisa decides that her friendship with Jessie is stronger than some embarrassing video and vows to remove the video once she has one. What's one more day?

At the academic decathlon, Jessie is being trolled by members of the opposing team. She rushes out to see her friends and questions whether she will be able to focus in light of the damage the video has done to her reputation. Kelly tells her not to worry about it and shows that she is now rocking the Jessie fashion mistake by having tucked her skirt into her panties. Zack and Slater are also joining the underwear movement by wearing their boxers outside their pants. Despite this show of solidarity, Jessie freezes and has to try and make up for points at the next day's events.

Lisa is true to her word and takes the video down once she has won the competition. The Fashion Channel calls and offers Lisa an interview. She is ecstatic, but her friends are disappointed. Lisa decides to talk to Jessie to clear the air. Slater takes her laptop to ensure that no more embarrassing videos of Jessie show up online.

At the library, Jessie accuses Lisa of putting the competition before their friendship. Lisa agrees and apologizes, which apparently makes everything okay. Later, Lisa overhears girls discussing Jessie in the bathroom and she realizes that she needs to do a little more to make things up with Jessie.

At the Fashion Channel, Lisa introduces her final video as part of her interview. She showcases the "Spano Skirt," which, of course, is a skirt tucked into panties. Kelly and Lisa exhibit this latest trend. The folks at Fashion Channel, however, are unimpressed and Lisa does not get her dream job.

Back at the Max, Lisa laments losing her dream job while Zack applauds being able to see Kelly's underwear. Jessie arrives and informs the group that she won the decathlon.
name: Fashion Don't

description: Prepare yourself for an entirely new kind of manga experience. Jenna Jackson, Girl Detective, is a sex comedy disguised as a detective story. In this first issue, Jenna and her best friend Chrissy McDougall must solve a bizarre marital crime involving a dysfunctional couple who totally piss her off. Not to mention a mysterious ghost of a long dead private investigator who keeps popping into her life at the most inappropriate times. It's enough to drive any school girl crazy!
name: The House of Fools

description: Jenna and her best friend Chrissy are back at it again in another naughty, fun-filled story. This time the severed head of a young man washes up on the shore of Boston's Waterfront Park. As usual the police have no clue what to do so they ask Jenna to help solve the crime. Meanwhile Chrissy seeks the advice of her priest on how to resolve a delicate personal request from her boyfriend. This book is definitely NOT for the politically correct!
name: Headless In Boston

description:
'JOSHUA BLACK is a dark comedy/fantasy series that follows a reluctant teenage deity who inherits the throne of Heaven.'

The only eligible, living descendant of Jesus Christ, seventeen-year-old Joshua Black has inherited Heaven's throne and all of the burdens that come with it. After a violent encounter with his abusive father the night before, Joshua, whose family had been devastated by a tragic accident years earlier, wakes to find that God has undone the terrible event that ruined their lives. Joshua quickly learns that it wasn't an abstract God who rectified the situation, but that he, himself, is responsible for all of the changes happening around him. He also discovers that he has been burdened with an immense amount of power and responsibility.

Several angels and divine beings take it upon themselves to mentor Joshua and show him the ropes, but their efforts are thwarted at every turn. An irresistible succubus has managed to get close to him by using her powers of seduction. Joshua's youth and inexperience leave him unsure whose motives are pure and who wants to use his powers for their own gain. While these two factions battle to gain the boy's trust, more sinister forces are at work.

Joshua Black is alive and his life is better than ever! His family has been miraculously reunited and he couldn’t be happier. His father is sober, his mother is alive, and he even has a sister. Things couldn't be going better for Joshua... But sadly, his perfect life was too good to be true. Joshua comes down with a disturbing case of deja vu before being ripped out of his happy existence and plunged head first into a new and terrifying reality. Things only get worse when angels, the devil and an insanely sexy succubus show up to help him navigate his destiny.

Meet the Warhawks: a team of cyborg superheroes sworn to protect the world using non-lethal force. It’s a code that will be tested in their first contact with the ultimate enemy, the villainous cyborg syndicate Maelstrom.

In the epic first issue of this debut series, Jefferson Caesar AKA Weapon, the Warhawks' soulful leader, welcomes Timothy Pendragon AKA Arsenal, to their ranks. Son of the Warhawks’ genius creator Dr. Pendragon, Timothy has abandoned his disease-ravaged body in favor of a dangerous transplant into a giant Mobile Assault Unit. It's a transformation that causes haunting side-effects in his consciousness that he struggles to keep under wraps.

The battle begins as Maelstrom attacks a next-generation space shuttle in search of the first critical component for their suitably sinister plan called Project Zeus. Our heroes quickly discover that Headhunter, a former ally, is leading the Maelstrom field missions with technology that can defeat the Warhawks.

Can the Warhawks code against lethal force survive in the face of superior weaponry, betrayal, and true evil?

Collecting the epic one shot and the first four issues of the ongoing series the Rampage Jackson Street Soldier Special Edition. Read as Rampage takes on all sorts of challenges including a menacing master of electricity and a quintet of super human henchmen. Watch as the break out super star of the Catalyst Prime Universe uses his super human powers to help those that need it the most and deliver powerful beat downs to those who need it even more! A great way to get caught up on what's going on with Rampage!
